00:01:25.433 --> 00:01:29.466
So my my channel is called Wendigoon
which is a combination of the words

00:01:29.466 --> 00:01:30.966
Wendigo and Goon.

00:01:30.966 --> 00:01:34.100
The Wendigo is a creature
from Native American folklore,

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:35.800
specifically the Algonquin tribe.

00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:39.600
It is, in their lore, a creature

00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:43.633
that develops when someone commits
an act of cannibalism.

00:01:43.633 --> 00:01:46.833
That if anyone gives in
to this inclination,

00:01:46.866 --> 00:01:49.800
this demonic spirit
or dark spirit will possess them.

00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:53.100
Something that's always interested me
about the Wendigo...

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:55.300
As a lot of the settlers came
in, the stories began to change about it.

00:01:55.300 --> 00:01:57.433
It went from this kind of spirit
of the woods

00:01:57.433 --> 00:02:00.300
to like this monster,
this thing that needed to be hunted down.

00:02:00.300 --> 00:02:03.300
It's something that's very personal
with me, but it's also the way that

00:02:03.300 --> 00:02:06.566
the legend of the Wendigo itself
has adapted and changed throughout time...

00:02:06.633 --> 00:02:08.900
And the way
I want to look at stories because of it.

00:02:10.366 --> 00:02:10.933
Perfect.

00:02:10.933 --> 00:02:14.066
Immediately. Fredrick
Knudsen with “Down the Rabbit Hole”.

00:02:14.100 --> 00:02:17.033
This is his video about Austrian wine
poisoning.

00:02:17.033 --> 00:02:19.933
