00:04:13.700 --> 00:04:15.266
It would be the “My house walk-through”.

00:04:15.266 --> 00:04:16.366
At the time I saw it,

00:04:16.366 --> 00:04:18.233
I almost thought that I had dreamt it.

00:04:18.233 --> 00:04:20.133
It's such a strange video.

00:04:24.466 --> 00:04:26.700
The original video is in Japanese,

00:04:26.700 --> 00:04:27.733
and from the subtitles,

00:04:27.733 --> 00:04:28.500
we can see that

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:29.433
it's an individual

00:04:29.433 --> 00:04:30.933
walking through an abandoned

00:04:30.933 --> 00:04:32.300
rundown house.

00:04:32.300 --> 00:04:34.133
Each time he walks through the house,

00:04:34.133 --> 00:04:35.566
it seems to be that

00:04:35.566 --> 00:04:37.300
there is a kind of looping going on

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:38.666
like some kind of time loop.

00:04:38.666 --> 00:04:39.933
He'll walk through the house again

00:04:39.933 --> 00:04:41.900
and he'll describe the same things over.

00:04:41.900 --> 00:04:43.300
But the house is more decrepit.

00:04:43.300 --> 00:04:45.266
Like if you skip to further,

00:04:45.266 --> 00:04:46.600
everything's covered in like this

00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:47.833
red growth now

00:04:47.833 --> 00:04:49.433
and it looks like something's

00:04:49.433 --> 00:04:51.366
eating the walls almost,

00:04:51.366 --> 00:04:53.700
but the narrator doesn't seem to notice.

00:04:53.700 --> 00:04:54.633
He's still describing

00:04:54.633 --> 00:04:55.800
the same things that he was before.

00:04:55.800 --> 00:04:56.600
He's still walking through them,

00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:58.166
but the house is getting worse.

00:04:58.166 --> 00:04:59.500
I think the thing that interests me

00:04:59.500 --> 00:05:00.200
so much

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:02.233
about being scared or like,

00:05:02.233 --> 00:05:04.133
you know, scary media in general

00:05:04.133 --> 00:05:06.633
is that art exists to elicit emotion

00:05:06.633 --> 00:05:09.000
and there are few emotions

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:12.033
you can get across as powerful as fear.

00:05:12.033 --> 00:05:13.466
Like you can make someone happy.

00:05:13.466 --> 00:05:15.033
Sure.  You can make someone sad.

00:05:15.033 --> 00:05:16.466
Those are pretty easy ones.

00:05:16.466 --> 00:05:18.100
But to really make someone afraid,

00:05:18.100 --> 00:05:19.100
that's something rare.

00:05:19.100 --> 00:05:20.433
That's something hard to get across.

