00:09:37.766 --> 00:09:39.033
And it's those details

00:09:39.033 --> 00:09:40.833
that I like so much about these stories.

00:09:40.833 --> 00:09:42.700
Looking at these rankings, I'm very happy with it,

00:09:42.700 --> 00:09:45.066
because fourth, we have Mista GG, 
taking these very disturbing, 

00:09:45.066 --> 00:09:47.266
scary things, making them not scary.

00:09:47.266 --> 00:09:48.800
We have a disappearance case,

00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:51.700
something that your mind can 
kind of wander with the grisly details of.

00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:54.766
And Nexpo also explains it in such a scary manner.

00:09:54.766 --> 00:09:58.533
Then we have Jacob Geller.  Giving me a
fear I didn’t know I had,

00:09:58.533 --> 00:10:01.500
about the cold and the horrors that humanity face because of it.

00:10:01.500 --> 00:10:02.200
And then at number one,

00:10:02.200 --> 00:10:03.400
we have a video that I thought

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:05.066
I hallucinated for several years.

00:10:05.066 --> 00:10:06.166
So I think

00:10:06.166 --> 00:10:07.900
I think that's a pretty solid list.

00:10:07.900 --> 00:10:09.000
So if you're looking for nightmares

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:10.200
this Halloween season,

00:10:10.200 --> 00:10:12.566
then pick any you want out of this list

00:10:12.566 --> 00:10:14.266
at your discretion, of course.

00:10:15.033 --> 00:10:17.433
It’s fascinating to me to 
go through these videos.

00:10:17.433 --> 00:10:20.166
You know, I only started doing YouTube a few years ago,

00:10:20.166 --> 00:10:21.066
and whenever I started,

00:10:21.066 --> 00:10:22.533
there were a lot of people who were like,

00:10:22.533 --> 00:10:24.100
oh, well, you know, ship sailed on that.

00:10:24.100 --> 00:10:25.266
And I would watch

00:10:25.266 --> 00:10:26.100
like several of the videos

00:10:26.100 --> 00:10:27.100
I've talked about today

00:10:27.100 --> 00:10:29.033
and be like, I want to be a YouTuber.

00:10:29.033 --> 00:10:30.433
I want to get I have stories to tell.

00:10:30.433 --> 00:10:31.500
I want to get those across.

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:34.166
I think a lot of people want to know

00:10:34.166 --> 00:10:35.633
why they're afraid of something, right?

00:10:35.633 --> 00:10:37.266
And things like that interest me so much.

00:10:37.266 --> 00:10:40.400
To understand why I’m afraid 
of the things that I’m afraid of.

00:10:40.400 --> 00:10:41.800
And as a storyteller,

00:10:41.800 --> 00:10:43.433
manipulate those to my advantage.

